Sentencas: Lanthanum-based iron- and cobalt-containing perovskite has a high potential as a cathode material because of its high electro-catalytic activity at a relatively low operating temperature in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) (600-800).
Titulo: Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 supported La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: To enhance the electro-catalytic reduction of oxidants on La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF), Ga doped ceria (Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95, GDC) supported LSCF (15LSCF/GDC) is successfully fabricated using an impregnation method with a ratio of 15 wt% LSCF and 85 wt% GDC.
Titulo: Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 supported La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cathodic polarization resistances of 15LSCF/GDC are 0.015 Omega cm(2), 0.03 Omega cm(2), 0.11 Omega cm(2), and 0.37 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C, 750 degrees C, 700 degrees C, and 650 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 supported La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The simply mixed composite cathode with LSCF and GDC of the same compositions shows 0.05 Omega cm(2), 0.2 Omega cm(2), 0.56 Omega cm(2), and 1.20 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C, 750 degrees C, 700 degrees C, and 650 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 supported La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The fuel cell performance of the SOFC with 15LSCF/GDC shows maximum power densities of 1.45 W cm(-2), 1.2W cm(-2), and 0.8W cm(-2) at 780 degrees C, 730 degrees C, and 680 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 supported La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: GDC supported LSCF (15LSCF/GDC) shows a higher fuel cell performance with small compositions of LSCF due to the extension of triple phase boundaries and effective building of an electronic path.
Titulo: Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 supported La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells
